The paper deals with the design of error-correcting codes, specifically non-binary quasi-cyclic LDPC codes, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of small fields, which is a topic in network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the algorithmic approach used in the paper falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
